oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photo postcard sent from Sgt. Connie Williams of Huntington
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A picture postcard showing a street scene with the title "AISEY-s/-SEINE / La Place de l'Eglise" imprinted in the upper right corner. A row of buildings on the right with sign on second building reading "DOCKS de L'UNION FRANCAISE." The address side of card has a short note from Sgt. Connie Marshall Williams, Co. E, 306th Engineer Regt. to Mrs. J. C. Moore of Lexington, Tennessee. Williams served in France and took part in the Meuse-Argonne offensive in the fall of 1918.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
